The paper deals with an algorithmic approach to solving the optimal transportation problem, which is a fundamental problem in learning and statistics. This problem has applications in many areas of computer science, including data science (cs.DS), machine learning (cs.LG), numerical analysis (cs.NA), information theory (cs.IT), and computational complexity (cs.CC). Therefore, these are the most likely sub-categories for this paper.
